news.title: China Evergrande shares fall after missing new coupon payments
news.para: Evergrande, whose $19 billion in international bonds are in cross-default after missing a deadline to pay coupons earlier this month, had new coupon payments worth $255 million due on Tuesday for its June 2023 and 2025 notes.

news.title: Lucknow civic body hikes budget to spruceup streetlight facility in city
news.para: The EC meeting was convened by Mayor Sanyukta Bhatia to revise budgetary allocations for various purposes after taking stock of the expenditure by the LMC during the current financial year so far.

news.title: Tamil Nadu: No more extension charges for new Tangedco meters
news.para: For instance, an apartment in Chennai, which is located a hundred metres away from an existing power line, paid .90,000 as extension cost for a new three-phase connection.

news.title: Chennai: Unauthorised portions of commercial building sealed at T Nagar
news.para: While planning permission was issued for construction of basement floor (partly shop and parking) and ground + three floors for a shopping complex, one more floor was added to the structure.

news.title: Gujarat HC orders Ahmedabad civic body not to evict Vasna slum dwellers
news.para: Thirty-five families from the slums filed a petition in the high court through advocate Manoj Shrimali, who submitted that they had made a representation on August 19 for alternative accommodation after the civic body decided to demolish the slums.

news.title: TNUHDB may scrap allotments of owners who rented out flats
news.para: The board officials said they have the provisions to penalize the owners of the houses given on rent and would also cancel their allotments.

news.title: Nashik civic body to act tough against property tax defaulters
news.para: The civic body has set a property tax collection target of Rs 140 crore for the current financial year, but so far has managed to collect only Rs 107 crore.

news.title: Prayagraj civic body launches OTS scheme for property tax defaulters
news.para: The state authorities issued a government order (GO) for OTS plan on December 27 after the Mayor of the city sent a proposal to state authorities for OTS approval. The scheme will be effective till March 31, 2022.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 12 residential, 37 commercial units sans BU permission
news.para: The sealed houses are near Al Mubarak Residency in Danilimda. The civic body’s town planning and estate department also sealed 37 commercial units in areas such as Kubernagar, Odhav and Shahpur.

news.title: CREDAI plans to pump in Rs 10,000 crore during Rajasthan summit-2022
news.para: Along with this, three industrial cities will be developed in Jaipur city, in which about 2,000 industries will be established. Two integrated townships will also be developed, which will have about 3,000 plots.

news.title: L&T Metro Rail Hyderabad raises Rs 13,119 crore
news.para: ET reported on December 22 that the company was raising up to Rs 13,600 crore including Rs 8,600 crore worth of bonds and CPs of up to Rs 5,000 crore.

news.title: Greater Noida: GNIDA penalises housing society over improper waste management
news.para: ​The action was taken against the Sri Radha Sky Garden society in Sector 16B of Greater Noida West on the instructions of GNIDA CEO Narendra Bhooshan following complaints by its residents, the officials said.

news.title: KGK Realty & Dhoot Infrastructure buys Sare Gurugram under IBC
news.para: The consortium outbid five others bidders, including realty companies Alpha Corp and Signature Global and high net worth individual investors Nikhil Jain, Sunil Kumar Jain and Summer Nanda, they said.

news.title: NRIs, OCIs do not need its prior nod to buy immovable property in India: RBI
news.para: ​The clarification has been issued by Reserve Bank of India (RBI) following queries received at its various offices with regard to acquisition of immovable properties by Overseas Citizens of India (OCIs) in the wake of a Supreme Court judgment relating to Foreign Exchange Regulation Act (FERA).

news.title: Smartworks leases 450,000 sq ft office space in Hyderabad
news.para: Smartworks has been lapping up office spaces across the country, with demand from enterprises driving the growth. The firm has added more than a million sq ft in 2021, with plans to double it in 2022.
